{"award_age":66.0,"bio_image":"full\/d97b57fbb0b6ba70ca972021641f363ecc7eb8c5.jpg","category":"Economics","country":"United States","date_of_birth":"1928-06-13T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":null,"gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/a\/a9\/John_Forbes_Nash%2C_Jr._by_Peter_Badge.jpg\/220px-John_Forbes_Nash%2C_Jr._by_Peter_Badge.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/John_Forbes_Nash","mini_bio":"<p><b>John Forbes Nash, Jr.<\/b> (June 13, 1928\u00a0\u2013 May 23, 2015) was an American <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Mathematician\" title=\"Mathematician\">mathematician<\/a> with fundamental contributions in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Game_theory\" title=\"Game theory\">game theory<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Differential_geometry\" title=\"Differential geometry\">differential geometry<\/a>, and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Partial_differential_equation\" title=\"Partial differential equation\">partial differential equations<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/John_Forbes_Nash#cite_note-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/John_Forbes_Nash#cite_note-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> Nash's work has provided insight into the factors that govern chance and decision making inside complex systems in daily life.<\/p><p>His theories are used in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Economics\" title=\"Economics\">economics<\/a>, computing, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Evolutionary_biology\" title=\"Evolutionary biology\">evolutionary biology<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Artificial_intelligence\" title=\"Artificial intelligence\">artificial intelligence<\/a>, accounting, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Computer_science\" title=\"Computer science\">computer science<\/a> (<a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Minimax_algorithm\" title=\"Minimax algorithm\" class=\"mw-redirect\">minimax algorithm<\/a> which is based on Nash Equilibrium), <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Games_of_skill\" title=\"Games of skill\" class=\"mw-redirect\">games of skill<\/a>, politics and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Military_theory\" title=\"Military theory\">military theory<\/a>. Serving as a Senior Research Mathematician at <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Princeton_University\" title=\"Princeton University\">Princeton University<\/a> during the latter part of his life, he shared the 1994 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Memorial_Prize_in_Economic_Sciences\" title=\"Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences\">Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences<\/a> with game theorists <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Reinhard_Selten\" title=\"Reinhard Selten\">Reinhard Selten<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/John_Harsanyi\" title=\"John Harsanyi\">John Harsanyi<\/a>. In 2015, he was awarded the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Abel_Prize\" title=\"Abel Prize\">Abel Prize<\/a> for his work on <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nonlinear_system\" title=\"Nonlinear system\">nonlinear<\/a> partial differential equations. John Nash has an Erdos number 3, according to the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/American_Mathematical_Society\" title=\"American Mathematical Society\">American Mathematical Society<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/John_Forbes_Nash#cite_note-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p>In 1959, Nash began showing clear signs of mental illness, and spent several years at psychiatric hospitals being treated for <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Paranoid_schizophrenia\" title=\"Paranoid schizophrenia\">paranoid schizophrenia<\/a>. After 1970, his condition slowly improved, allowing him to return to academic work by the mid-1980s.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Nasar1994_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/John_Forbes_Nash#cite_note-Nasar1994-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> His struggles with his illness and his recovery became the basis for <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Sylvia_Nasar\" title=\"Sylvia Nasar\">Sylvia Nasar<\/a>'s biography, <i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/A_Beautiful_Mind_(book)\" title=\"A Beautiful Mind (book)\">A Beautiful Mind<\/a><\/i>, as well as a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/A_Beautiful_Mind_(film)\" title=\"A Beautiful Mind (film)\">film of the same name<\/a> starring <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Russell_Crowe\" title=\"Russell Crowe\">Russell Crowe<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Oscar_race_scrutinizes_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/John_Forbes_Nash#cite_note-Oscar_race_scrutinizes-6\"><span>[<\/span>6<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/John_Forbes_Nash#cite_note-7\"><span>[<\/span>7<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/John_Forbes_Nash#cite_note-8\"><span>[<\/span>8<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p>On May 23, 2015, Nash and his wife, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Alicia_Nash\" title=\"Alicia Nash\">Alicia Nash<\/a>, while riding in a taxi, were killed in a motor vehicle accident in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/New_Jersey\" title=\"New Jersey\">New Jersey<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-NYT_death_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/John_Forbes_Nash#cite_note-NYT_death-9\"><span>[<\/span>9<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"John Forbes Nash","place_of_birth":"Bluefield, West Virginia, United States","place_of_death":null,"text":"John Forbes Nash , Economics, 1994","year":1994.0}